## Rocket Launch Viewing

**Price**: $99/person<br>
**Launch Date**: Wednesday, June 5 at 7:00AM CDT (12:00 UTC)<br>
**Key Times**: Checkin 5:00AM | Boarding 5:30AM | Departure 6:00AM<br>
**Location**: [Sea Ranch Marina, 33256 State Park Rd 100, South Padre Island, TX](https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Original+Dolphin+Watch/@26.0766846,-97.1657479,20.12z/data=!4m15!1m8!3m7!1s0x866fadc294094ce7:0x7ab6b6ccd06a1c44!2s33256+State+Park+Rd+100,+South+Padre+Island,+TX+78597!3b1!8m2!3d26.0771636!4d-97.1663996!16s%2Fg%2F11cncjgrfd!3m5!1s0x866fadc2794a59b7:0x4c876b81f32e6223!8m2!3d26.076626!4d-97.165552!16s%2Fg%2F1txc7gjf?entry=ttu)<br>

* Great location to view all the key events of the launch
* Around 4 miles / 7 km from launch pad
* Clear view of pad, rocket, liftoff and ascent
* Stable vessel, calm seas and open deck for excellent viewing
* Free parking, a guaranteed spot and no need to show up many hours early
<br>
<br>
**DELAY/SCRUB POLICY:** *Tickets are generally non-refundable.*<br>
Per agreement with our captains, if there is a delay announced prior to the day of launch, your ticket will be valid for the new launch date and time.
If you canâ€™t make the backup date, you will be responsible for selling your ticket to others on standby, and we can help facilitate that as well.
If a launch day delay is officially announced later than 12 midnight CDT on the day of the launch trip (6 hours prior to departure), or if a passenger does not show up by the published boarding time, the boat will go out as scheduled, tickets will be considered used and will no longer be refundable.
Conversely, case there is an issue with the boat or weather keeping us from departing for the launch, and it occurs as scheduled, a full refund will be issued.
